00:25:30.111 --> 00:25:32.155
I don't appreciate
having my arm twisted.

261
00:25:38.703 --> 00:25:40.580
What are you even looking for.
Trooper?

262
00:25:43.667 --> 00:25:45.335
Take a nickel's worth
of free advice.

263
00:25:46.711 --> 00:25:47.754
go home.

264
00:27:10.503 --> 00:27:11.713
Hello.

265
00:27:11.755 --> 00:27:13.214
Yeah. hello.

266
00:27:13.256 --> 00:27:15.383
Is this Trooper Archer?
Jane Archer?

267
00:27:16.009 --> 00:27:17.802
Yeah. who is this?

268
00:27:17.844 --> 00:27:19.846
This is Agent Becky Collins.

269
00:27:19.888 --> 00:27:22.891
We crossed paths at the FBI
field office earlier.

270
00:27:23.600 --> 00:27:25.560
I'm thinking maybe
we should talk.

271
00:27:29.147 --> 00:27:30.523
- There you go.
- Thanks.

272
00:27:39.032 --> 00:27:40.825
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

273
00:27:41.618 --> 00:27:44.496
I really appreciate
you meeting with me.

274
00:27:44.537 --> 00:27:46.748
Yeah. Well. next round
is definitely on you.

275
00:27:46.790 --> 00:27:49.626
If Zolan knew I was walking
you through this. he'd. uh...

276
00:27:51.086 --> 00:27:52.587
Screw it.

277
00:27:53.129 --> 00:27:55.632
As we know. the first killings
were 16 days ago.

278
00:27:56.174 --> 00:27:58.718
Death Valley Junction.
A tiny place.

279
00:27:58.760 --> 00:28:01.012
He dismembered the Durk's
Paint shopkeeper there.

280
00:28:02.639 --> 00:28:04.683
Stole money.
credit card numbers.

281
00:28:04.724 --> 00:28:06.226
tools. clothing. food.

282
00:28:07.268 --> 00:28:10.188
The victims he chooses. there
are those of pure opportunity

283
00:28:10.230 --> 00:28:12.065
and those he takes
something specific from.

284
00:28:12.107 --> 00:28:14.234
like the pharmacist
from Colorado.

285
00:28:14.275 --> 00:28:17.195
Yeah. he'll kill for
painkillers and psychotropics.

286
00:28:17.237 --> 00:28:19.698
Percocet. Percodan. OxyContin.

287
00:28:19.739 --> 00:28:21.324
We don't think he's dealing.

288
00:28:21.366 --> 00:28:23.535
He's taking these drugs
himself. All of them.

289
00:28:24.077 --> 00:28:26.579
And the gun shop
in. uh. Nevada. was it?

290
00:28:26.621 --> 00:28:28.581
That's him.
He broke in after hours.

291
00:28:28.623 --> 00:28:32.502
Got away with
at least one pistol.
a shotgun. plenty of ammo

292
00:28:32.544 --> 00:28:34.546
and the shop's owner
was a collector.

293
00:28:34.587 --> 00:28:37.173
He had a secret stash
of hand grenades.

294
00:28:37.215 --> 00:28:38.299
Now. all missing.

295
00:28:38.341 --> 00:28:40.719
-Jesus.
-Mm-hmm. Yeah.

296
00:28:40.760 --> 00:28:44.222
And. um. the library
in Cedar City. Utah.

297
00:28:44.264 --> 00:28:47.225
He killed the security guard
and the librarian.

298
00:28:47.726 --> 00:28:49.936
Yeah. We got that surveillance.

299
00:28:52.188 --> 00:28:54.441
What did he want
from a public library

300
00:28:54.482 --> 00:28:56.359
that he couldn't get
off the Internet?

301
00:28:56.401 --> 00:28:59.028
Well. if there's one
thing the FBI still does well.

302
00:28:59.070 --> 00:29:00.822
it's track the Internet.

303
00:29:00.864 --> 00:29:02.532
and he's not on it.

304
00:29:02.574 --> 00:29:05.618
He took exactly two books
from a set of encyclopedias.

305
00:29:05.660 --> 00:29:06.911
"N" and "T."

306
00:29:06.953 --> 00:29:07.996
"N" and "T."

307
00:29:09.914 --> 00:29:12.000
His mission.
if he even has a mission.

308
00:29:12.041 --> 00:29:14.252
has him heading east
from motel to motel.

309
00:29:14.294 --> 00:29:16.129
Sometimes spending whole days
in one place.

310
00:29:16.963 --> 00:29:18.923
How do you know
he's been staying at motels?

311
00:29:18.965 --> 00:29:21.718
I assumed he'd been living
in his vehicle.

312
00:29:21.760 --> 00:29:24.721
If you want. I can show you.

313
00:29:41.905 --> 00:29:44.574
He was here three days ago.
Three days after Kansas.

314
00:29:44.616 --> 00:29:46.242
Checked in
in the dead of night.

315
00:29:46.284 --> 00:29:47.619
On foot. paid cash.

316
00:29:48.077 --> 00:29:50.038
Hotel clerk was a total stoner.

317
00:29:50.079 --> 00:29:51.539
Couldn't give a description.

318
00:29:51.581 --> 00:29:54.125
Didn't even have him register.
Worthless.

319
00:29:54.626 --> 00:29:56.377
Middle of the next day.
the maid ignored

320
00:29:56.419 --> 00:29:57.962
the "Do not disturb" sign
on the doorknob

321
00:29:58.004 --> 00:30:00.965
or didn't see it somehow.
let herself in.

322
00:30:14.479 --> 00:30:16.606
He used an axe.
cut her in half.

323
00:30:18.024 --> 00:30:20.652
This seems to have gotten
his creative juices flowing.

324
00:30:21.903 --> 00:30:23.863
This is how he leaves
all the crime scenes.

325
00:30:26.491 --> 00:30:28.618
"Open the gates."

326
00:30:30.870 --> 00:30:34.082
Our analysts say
he's obsessed with having
his achievements seen.

327
00:30:37.293 --> 00:30:38.461
Can I use your computer?

328
00:30:42.340 --> 00:30:44.050
Take a look at this.

329
00:30:44.092 --> 00:30:46.344
It's from those murders
in Harrisburg. Pennsylvania.

330
00:30:46.386 --> 00:30:47.762
Church killings. years ago.

331
00:30:47.804 --> 00:30:50.640
He was a satanist.
Richard Reeves.

332
00:30:50.682 --> 00:30:53.184
Richard Joshua Reeves.
He killed 13 people.

333
00:30:53.226 --> 00:30:54.686
Similar profile.

334
00:30:54.727 --> 00:30:56.604
We're aware.

335
00:30:56.646 --> 00:30:59.440
Those kind of satanic symbols
and phrases do tend to overlap.

336
00:30:59.482 --> 00:31:02.402
but our guy.
he's not really copycatting.

337
00:31:02.443 --> 00:31:05.280
Reeves was a mass murderer.
not serial.

338
00:31:07.282 --> 00:31:09.284
Maybe an admirer
of Reeves. at least.

339
00:31:10.577 --> 00:31:11.995
Inspired by him.

340
00:31:12.954 --> 00:31:15.582
Okay. judging by the distances
he's been traveling.

341
00:31:15.623 --> 00:31:18.793
in the next day or two. this
is where he'll actually be.

342
00:31:18.835 --> 00:31:21.754
Somewhere between
Columbus. Ohio.
and Wheeling. West Virginia.

343
00:31:21.796 --> 00:31:24.841
110 miles. 25 exits.
give or take.

344
00:31:25.508 --> 00:31:28.011
This is the best chance anyone
has of running him down.

345
00:31:29.929 --> 00:31:32.390
Well. I don't know if
it's right to wish you luck.

346
00:31:32.432 --> 00:31:35.101
so I'll just say be careful.

347
00:31:36.978 --> 00:31:38.521
Thanks for sticking
your neck out.

348
00:31:38.563 --> 00:31:41.065
I wish there was some way
I could repay the favor.

349
00:31:42.108 --> 00:31:43.610
I'll pass your theories along.

350
00:31:43.651 --> 00:31:45.737
For all the good that'll do.

351
00:32:02.462 --> 00:32:04.714
I'm not allowed
to be telling you
what I'm about to tell you.

352
00:32:04.756 --> 00:32:07.300
There's a small construction
and demolition company

353
00:32:07.342 --> 00:32:08.426
near Kansas City.

354
00:32:09.302 --> 00:32:11.346
A quantity of explosives
were stolen.

355
00:32:12.096 --> 00:32:13.014
Explosives?

356
00:32:13.056 --> 00:32:14.307
Dynamite.

357
00:32:14.766 --> 00:32:18.144
About 20 pounds or so
of old-school. volatile TNT.

358
00:32:18.186 --> 00:32:20.855
Enough to do
significant damage.

359
00:32:23.232 --> 00:32:24.817
Manson and "The Family."

360
00:32:24.859 --> 00:32:27.195
as the cult members
called themselves.

361
00:32:27.236 --> 00:32:30.406
killed seven people
in the infamous
Tate-LaBianca murders of 1969.

362
00:32:30.448 --> 00:32:33.826
Messages were left written
on the walls in blood.

363
00:32:34.661 --> 00:32:37.497
Devil worship was also
the motive 20 years ago.

364
00:32:37.538 --> 00:32:41.501
when teenager
Richard Joshua Reeves
committed the grisly killings

365
00:32:41.542 --> 00:32:44.253
at Christ Cross Church
in Harrisburg. Pennsylvania.

366
00:32:44.295 --> 00:32:47.090
Reeves murdered 13 hostages
inside the church.

367
00:32:47.131 --> 00:32:48.716
including a priest.

368
00:32:48.758 --> 00:32:50.677
while performing
what authorities described

369
00:32:50.760 --> 00:32:52.804
as a ritualistic black mass.

370
00:33:05.608 --> 00:33:07.986
Slasher.
killing all those people.

371
00:33:08.027 --> 00:33:11.030
When this is over. you wanna
know who's gonna be behind it?

372
00:33:11.072 --> 00:33:12.532
The government.

373
00:33:12.573 --> 00:33:14.617
I read on 8chan
how our government.

374
00:33:14.659 --> 00:33:17.704
they've been keeping criminals
in secret military prisons

375
00:33:17.745 --> 00:33:19.539
for doing experiments on.

376
00:33:19.580 --> 00:33:21.749
Now one of those criminals
finally escaped.

377
00:33:22.458 --> 00:33:24.335
Z100.5. we'll begin another

378
00:33:24.377 --> 00:33:27.797
commercial-free block
of smooth jazz in a moment.

379
00:33:27.839 --> 00:33:30.425
But first. the Satanic Slasher.

380
00:34:17.597 --> 00:34:18.681
Hello?

381
00:34:23.686 --> 00:34:24.771
Can I help you?

382
00:34:43.414 --> 00:34:44.457
I'm listening.

383
00:34:46.167 --> 00:34:48.086
I've always liked priests.

384
00:34:49.712 --> 00:34:51.380
When I was just a young boy.

385
00:34:52.256 --> 00:34:55.927
my priest.
he took me under his wing.

386
00:34:57.720 --> 00:34:59.097
You could say

387
00:35:00.056 --> 00:35:02.558
that he made me into the man
that I am today.

388
00:35:02.600 --> 00:35:04.936
Oh. that's good. my son.
Very good.

389
00:35:05.520 --> 00:35:07.688
And have you come to.
uh. confess?

390
00:35:09.690 --> 00:35:12.401
-Not exactly.
-Pardon me?

391
00:36:14.297 --> 00:36:16.924
Congratulations.

392
00:36:20.803 --> 00:36:22.638
Oh. Thank you.

393
00:36:25.975 --> 00:36:28.436
That reminds me. um.

394
00:36:28.477 --> 00:36:30.313
could I get a glass of milk.
please?

395
00:36:33.941 --> 00:36:35.359
Thank you.

396
00:37:17.485 --> 00:37:19.070
Jesus.

397
00:37:19.111 --> 00:37:20.613
Richard Joshua Reeves

398
00:37:20.655 --> 00:37:23.074
slaughtered the 13 men
and women

399
00:37:23.115 --> 00:37:25.868
he briefly held hostage
inside the church
that March afternoon.

400
00:37:25.910 --> 00:37:29.038
He claimed that
human sacrifice was necessary

401
00:37:29.080 --> 00:37:32.375
to. quote. "fulfill
his obligation to Satan."

402
00:37:32.959 --> 00:37:35.294
In a coordinated siege
upon the church.

403
00:37:35.336 --> 00:37:37.380
Harrisburg police officers

404
00:37:37.421 --> 00:37:40.007
managed to capture
Reeves alive.

405
00:37:40.049 --> 00:37:43.094
In 2004.
facing a death sentence.

406
00:37:43.135 --> 00:37:45.179
Reeves finally met his end

407
00:37:45.221 --> 00:37:48.933
when he was shot and killed
while attacking a prison guard

408
00:37:48.975 --> 00:37:51.102
in the federal penitentiary
where he was held.

409
00:37:52.645 --> 00:37:55.564
We're asking all the major
East Coast hotel chains

410
00:37:55.606 --> 00:37:56.857
to help us find the Slasher.

411
00:37:56.899 --> 00:37:58.567
Yes. sir.

412
00:37:58.609 --> 00:38:00.486
The suspect is almost
certainly a white male.

413
00:38:02.071 --> 00:38:04.073
Above average height.
stocky build.

414
00:38:04.115 --> 00:38:06.409
will be traveling alone.
pays in cash.

415
00:38:06.450 --> 00:38:10.788
Whatever you do.
do not confront this man.

416
00:38:10.830 --> 00:38:12.540
If you have suspicions

417
00:38:12.581 --> 00:38:13.708
about a guest
you feel fits the description.

418
00:38:13.749 --> 00:38:15.042
call 911.

419
00:38:15.960 --> 00:38:18.254
Afternoon. sir. Officer Archer.

420
00:38:19.088 --> 00:38:22.300
I'm sorry to trouble you. but
we'd actually like some help

421
00:38:22.341 --> 00:38:24.635
watching out for
the interstate killer.

422
00:38:24.677 --> 00:38:25.678
The Slasher.

423
00:38:25.720 --> 00:38:27.513
Oh.

424
00:38:27.555 --> 00:38:29.557
What little information
we have. I'd like to run by you

425
00:38:29.682 --> 00:38:31.934
in case any of your guests
match the profile.

426
00:38:31.976 --> 00:38:35.021
He'd be a white male. alone.
paid in cash most likely.

427
00:38:35.980 --> 00:38:38.274
Police have made it sound like

428
00:38:38.316 --> 00:38:40.234
he's likely not gonna
come around here.

429
00:38:40.276 --> 00:38:42.153
Yeah. uh. I'm starting to think

430
00:38:42.194 --> 00:38:43.779
they're probably right
about that actually.

431
00:38:43.821 --> 00:38:45.823
And I wasn't working
the desk last night

432
00:38:45.865 --> 00:38:47.366
so I don't know
how helpful I can be.

433
00:38:47.408 --> 00:38:48.784
I...

434
00:38:48.826 --> 00:38:50.161
I can check the register.

435
00:38:50.202 --> 00:38:51.787
We still have
our guests sign in.

436
00:38:54.832 --> 00:38:56.625
There's no one staying alone.

437
00:38:56.667 --> 00:38:59.420
All right. Uh. maybe I'll just
leave you my number.

438
00:38:59.462 --> 00:39:01.005
Um. thanks for your time.

439
00:39:01.881 --> 00:39:03.424
Oh. There's one gentleman.

440
00:39:03.466 --> 00:39:05.468
Uh...

441
00:39:05.509 --> 00:39:08.179
Checked in last night. Alone.

442
00:39:09.263 --> 00:39:10.931
Uh. Mr. Reeves.

443
00:39:12.808 --> 00:39:14.310
What did you say?

444
00:39:14.352 --> 00:39:17.063
Uh. Reeves.
Late last night. R.J. Reeves.

445
00:39:17.563 --> 00:39:19.190
-May I... May I look at that?
-Yep.

446
00:39:23.027 --> 00:39:24.070
Room 105?

447
00:39:24.528 --> 00:39:27.698
Go down the hall.
make a left. Outside.

448
00:39:28.240 --> 00:39:29.909
Okay. I'm gonna need
that key. sir.

449
00:39:32.787 --> 00:39:35.873
Okay. you call the police. you
tell them the Slasher is here.

450
00:39:35.915 --> 00:39:38.292
This is not a prank call.
This is for real.

451
00:39:39.293 --> 00:39:40.586
Call them now.

452
00:46:33.207 --> 00:46:34.208
Hello.

453
00:46:34.875 --> 00:46:36.418
Hello.

454
00:46:36.460 --> 00:46:39.046
I saw your answer
in the newspaper.

455
00:46:40.005 --> 00:46:41.882
Oh. so you're one of
our brethren. huh?

456
00:46:41.924 --> 00:46:44.092
Looking for someone
to lend you a hand?

457
00:46:44.134 --> 00:46:47.095
I'm looking for friends
who share my affinity
for discretion.

458
00:46:47.721 --> 00:46:49.431
I need help finding someone.

459
00:46:49.473 --> 00:46:51.141
but it needs to
be done discreetly.

460
00:46:51.600 --> 00:46:53.393
And it needs to stay offline.

461
00:46:53.936 --> 00:46:55.103
Where are you?

462
00:46:55.562 --> 00:46:57.147
Pennsylvania.

463
00:46:57.189 --> 00:46:59.441
Well. you're not far
from us actually.

464
00:46:59.483 --> 00:47:01.860
Why don't you come
talk to us tonight?

465
00:47:01.902 --> 00:47:06.740
Mr. Pendleton happens
to be hosting
some of his latest associates.

466
00:47:17.000 --> 00:47:19.127
Hi. Agent Collins.
it's Jane Archer.

467
00:47:19.169 --> 00:47:20.629
I'm on my way to Baltimore

468
00:47:20.671 --> 00:47:23.632
tracking a 410
area code number.

469
00:47:23.674 --> 00:47:25.467
If there is any way
you can help me out

470
00:47:25.509 --> 00:47:27.845
by matching an address
to this number.

471
00:47:27.886 --> 00:47:29.930
I'd hugely appreciate it.

472
00:47:33.475 --> 00:47:34.768
Hi.

473
00:47:35.227 --> 00:47:38.564
The gate's broken.
Just one sec.

474
00:47:40.983 --> 00:47:44.403
It used to open
by itself. but now it doesn't.

475
00:47:47.489 --> 00:47:48.615
There you go.

476
00:47:52.953 --> 00:47:54.371
Let me get that for you. I--

477
00:47:58.292 --> 00:48:00.002
Okey dokey.
Um. I was just gonna take it.

478
00:48:00.043 --> 00:48:01.503
I was gonna put it
in the back. but...

479
00:48:04.089 --> 00:48:05.757
Not a problem.

480
00:48:05.799 --> 00:48:06.884
You sit right there.

481
00:48:09.720 --> 00:48:11.972
Oh. uh. what did you say
your name was again?

482
00:48:12.556 --> 00:48:13.682
Richard.

483
00:48:13.724 --> 00:48:15.684
Well. Richard.

484
00:48:16.643 --> 00:48:18.562
first I have to ask.
for my own protection

485
00:48:18.604 --> 00:48:20.355
and the protection
of my employer...

486
00:48:22.399 --> 00:48:23.650
are you a cop?

487
00:48:25.319 --> 00:48:26.445
Policeman?

488
00:48:27.613 --> 00:48:29.448
-No.
-Okay.

489
00:48:29.489 --> 00:48:31.366
Because if you are
and you say you're not.

490
00:48:31.408 --> 00:48:33.201
that's just. um. like...

491
00:48:34.745 --> 00:48:35.746
Anyway.

492
00:48:36.580 --> 00:48:40.834
I guess however we can help
a fellow believer. we will.

493
00:48:43.211 --> 00:48:45.213
You know about us
using the classifieds.

494
00:48:47.174 --> 00:48:49.217
We're all in this together.
right?

495
00:48:49.760 --> 00:48:51.136
I need information.

496
00:48:51.678 --> 00:48:54.181
Yeah. well. Mr. Pendleton
will give you an earful.

497
00:48:54.640 --> 00:48:56.183
Enlightenment. more like.

498
00:48:56.892 --> 00:48:59.394
He is a great magus. He is.

499
00:48:59.937 --> 00:49:03.398
He keeps that on the down-low
these days. obviously.

500
00:49:03.440 --> 00:49:05.817
But he says he's got
a good feeling about you.

501
00:49:05.859 --> 00:49:07.778
you know. good vibrations.

502
00:49:08.362 --> 00:49:09.655
You are his invited guest

503
00:49:09.696 --> 00:49:11.323
so he's just excited
to meet ya.

504
00:49:12.032 --> 00:49:14.117
And I'm. uh. Marvin.
by the way.

505
00:49:15.702 --> 00:49:16.745
Come on.

506
00:49:19.915 --> 00:49:22.584
You've heard of Mr. Pendleton.
right?

507
00:49:24.294 --> 00:49:26.630
Yeah. he made his money
in the supermarket biz.

508
00:49:27.172 --> 00:49:28.215
years ago.

509
00:49:30.300 --> 00:49:32.928
You can set that down
right there if you'd like.

510
00:49:35.514 --> 00:49:38.600
Or keep it with you. Whatever.

511
00:49:39.226 --> 00:49:41.103
Uh... Just follow me.

512
00:49:42.604 --> 00:49:43.647
Come on.

513
00:49:47.526 --> 00:49:49.403
...in the middle
of the forest.

514
00:49:49.444 --> 00:49:51.113
and it's on a river.
